title: Installation Guide
sentences: Nate's Services  HelpInstallation guideThis page will guide you on the steps to take to successfully install and run our bot!
If you ever have any questions click here to access our support options.
IntroductionToday we will help you successfully install, run, and configure our mission chief bot!
Operating SystemsMissionchief Bot is currently only tested on the windows Operating System.
Operating SystemVersionSupportedWindows11âœ…10âœ…DependenciesPython 3.

x (Recommended)InstallationOption 1 - Using the CLIThe following steps explains how to install the Missionchief Bot using the Command Line Interface (CLI)Step 1 -  Downloading the BotFirst step is to of course download the botWhen on the download page you can either Download the Latest Version or scroll and download a previous version.
After finding the version you want it should navigate you to the correct download link.
All you have to do is wait 5 seconds and the file will be downloaded automatically!
Step 2 - Extracting the botAll you have to do is find the downloaded zip file, and extract it to a folder of your choice!
Step 3 (Optional) - Creating the venv!
First, you want to open the CLI of your choice, for this example I use Command PromptRun the command python -m venv .
venvThen you want to activate the venv using .
venv\Scripts\activateStep 4 - Installing the requirementsIf you created a venv make sure it's activatedAll you have to do is run the command pip install -r requirements.
txtStep 5 - Configuring the botFirst thing first, you want to open the config.
ini and edit the line username and password and set it to your email/username and password.
Step 6 - Running the botAll you have to do is run python main.
py and if you followed the steps correctly it should start running!
Option 2 - Using the Missionchief Bot.
exeStep 1 - Downloading the BotFirst step is to of course download the botWhen on the download page you can either Download the Latest Version or scroll and download a previous version.
After finding the version you want it should navigate you to the correct download link.
All you have to do is wait 5 seconds and the file will be downloaded automatically!
Step 2 - Extracting the botAll you have to do is find the downloaded zip file, and extract it to a folder of your choice!
Step 3 - Run the exe fileFirst double-click the bot, no administrator access is required.
Next Click the "edit config.
ini" button to customize the configNow just click the "start bot" and the exe will handle the rest!
